Program: Last Word
Title: Cec Thompson, Dekha Ibrahim Abdi, Robert Ettinger and Googie Withers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b012r99v
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 31 Jul 2011
Matthew Bannister on Cec Thompson - the first black man to play rugby league for Great Britain, he overcame a troubled childhood to become an inspirational teacher and successful businessman. Also Dekha Ibrahim Abdi who won international awards for her work in bringing peace and reconciliation to her native Kenya Robert Ettinger who pioneered cryonics and has now been frozen along with his two wives and his mother. Germany's answer to Rupert Murdoch - media tycoon Leo Kirch And the stage and screen actress Googie Withers. Show less